caption: Foundation rooms are generally pretty cool and the New Orleans location is no exception. But the old blonde bartender here is always a bit rude and persnickety... & I mean for like 6 or 7 times.

Very cool get hidden in the French Quarter. Service is amazing. Cocktails were creative and taste good. The duck I had was awesome and my friends all enjoy their meals.

Attended a company party at the Foundation Room and it was wonderful. The service at the bar was exceptional and they handle a busy crowd with ease. The food was delicious, especially the pork spare ribs. If you get the chance to go you should definitely enjoy the experience! :D

Fortunately, I had proof of the purchase, and the host, Sybil, was amazing at helping me out that night. Not only is this venue unique, but the staff in this room really treats it like a true VIP experience.  Thank you so much!

Had the best time in NOLA. The meat was perfectly cooked. We ordered crab cakes and chicken tikka skewers. The crab cakes just melted in the mouth. The fries were fantastic, we just stuffed ourselves with fries. The drinks weren't the best we had. Would have been a 5 star experience if the drinks complimented the food.

HOB, one of the best venues for live music. They used to have great shows CONSTANTLY.  Now it's a little more hit and miss. But it is a great place when your favorite act turns up.

This is THE place for an upscale adult experience. I was greeted with a glass of champagne. You have to make reservations as they do not let anyone in. Dress code enforced! It also boasts an elegant dining room. Check it out before a show in the music hall!
Nice place.
Friendly staff good music

When I say we had a great experience, I mean it! We called because we aren't members to make sure we could get a reservation and that was no issue! I found the place easily. It does have an exclusive feel because there's a very nice man who buzzed us in then let us on the elevator up. The ambiance is 11/10. The second host gave us some champagne because it is our honeymoon! We sat in the lounge for a minute to listen to some music. Then we had a romantic booth and two great servers who really made it even more pleasant. Then there was the food! I stuffed myself because I just had to keep tasting that pork chop! So juicy! Recommend every second especially for a special occasion.
This is one of the best places to go for some food and some drinks. They will make sure your time there is above and beyond. Always a great time ! Thank you

When you need to get out of the ordinary and experience something exclusive. Bartenders and staff are the best!
Foundation room is always an uplifting experience. The staff is highly professional the bartenders are on point. One thing for sure is the shows never disappoint !

I'm giving this is a five and taking one star off for service that was a little weird. Five because the food and the atmosphere were so amazing. You really have to go to this place, especially if you appreciate a deep luxurious 19th century fantasy feel, or goth with color. And food is some of the most delicious food I've had at a restaurant, and I eat out a lot. But as I said the service was a little weird. The server put his hand on my shoulder, which I didn't appreciate. He left the check in front of my date, and then after I gave him my credit card, gave it back to her to sign. Maybe he thought he saw a reason to do those things, but I didn't like it, and I ruminated about it afterwards, when I should have been thinking about the meal itself.
Love the HOB! And the foundation room is awesome

The decor was eclectic but very cool. We had truffle fries, Lollipop Chicken and crab cakes. All of the food was amazing.  The bartender was on point my Old Fashioned was perfect.  The street emptied and our server was quickly overwhelmed. Needed more servers for the French Quarter Fest.
Attentive staff, great ambience, food and drink. Excellent place to start your weekend and see a show at the House of Blues.
